I believe--well sometimes it's

00:36:24.724 --> 00:36:26.329
philia and sometimes
agape.

00:36:26.329 --> 00:36:29.199
Student: 
&gt;

00:36:29.199 --> 00:36:32.496
Prof: Okay,
in the epistles it's almost

00:36:32.496 --> 00:36:34.110
always agape.
 

00:36:34.110 --> 00:36:39.340
Any other questions?
 

00:36:39.340 --> 00:36:41.346
In other words,
what I'm reading in 1 John is

00:36:41.346 --> 00:36:43.489
representing again a radical
sectarian group.

00:36:43.489 --> 00:36:46.269
These are people who see
themselves as a community set

00:36:46.269 --> 00:36:47.530
apart from the cosmos.
 

00:36:47.530 --> 00:36:50.041
The cosmos is a place of
darkness and a place of the

00:36:50.041 --> 00:36:51.570
devil and that sort of thing.
 

00:36:51.570 --> 00:36:55.309
In fact--so now what is the
cause of this radical

00:36:55.309 --> 00:36:56.480
sectarianism?
 

00:36:56.480 --> 00:36:59.039
This is the most interesting
problem of the letter.

00:36:59.039 --> 00:37:04.199
Look at 2:18:
Children, it is the last hour.

00:37:04.199 --> 00:37:07.405
As you have heard that the
antichrist is coming,

00:37:07.405 --> 00:37:09.860
so now many antichrists have
come.

00:37:09.860 --> 00:37:14.110
There are these antichrists,
and notice it says:

00:37:14.110 --> 00:37:17.099
They went out from among us but
they did not belong to us.

00:37:17.099 --> 00:37:20.456
For if they had belonged to us
they would have remained in us,

00:37:20.456 --> 00:37:23.759
but by going out they made it
plain that none of them belongs

00:37:23.759 --> 00:37:24.309
to us.
 

00:37:24.309 --> 00:37:28.920
The people he's calling
antichrist are people that used

00:37:28.920 --> 00:37:34.213
to members of his own community
and they left the community for

00:37:34.213 --> 00:37:35.579
some reason.
 

00:37:35.579 --> 00:37:39.215
Now look at 2:22,
"Who is the liar but the

00:37:39.215 --> 00:37:43.010
one who denies that Jesus is the
Christ."

00:37:43.010 --> 00:37:45.893
He's saying you must believe
that Jesus is the Messiah,

00:37:45.893 --> 00:37:48.190
that's one thing,
is that the only thing?

00:37:48.190 --> 00:37:50.400
Not necessarily;
this is the antichrist,

00:37:50.400 --> 00:37:53.469
"The one who denies the
Father and the Son,"

00:37:53.469 --> 00:37:55.306
so some people,
he's saying,

00:37:55.306 --> 00:37:58.994
have left the community because
their Christology is not high

00:37:58.994 --> 00:37:59.610
enough.
 

00:37:59.610 --> 00:38:02.135
They're not allowing the true
sonship of Jesus,

00:38:02.135 --> 00:38:04.768
they're not allowing the
Messiahship of Jesus;

00:38:04.768 --> 00:38:07.768
maybe you're saying he's just a
prophet or he's just a human

00:38:07.768 --> 00:38:10.309
being, that's one of the things
that's going on.

00:38:10.309 --> 00:38:14.728
Look at 5:1:
Everyone who believes that

00:38:14.728 --> 00:38:17.280
Jesus is the Christ has been
born of God.

00:38:17.280 --> 00:38:19.940
Everyone who loves the parent
loves the child.

00:38:19.940 --> 00:38:23.804
That's the main part about
Jesus being the Christ,

00:38:23.804 --> 00:38:27.746
but now look at 4:2,
I'll start at the beginning of

00:38:27.746 --> 00:38:30.326
chapter 4:
Beloved, do not believe every

00:38:30.326 --> 00:38:33.213
spirit but test the spirits to
see whether they are from God,

00:38:33.213 --> 00:38:35.909
for many false prophets have
gone out into the world.

00:38:35.909 --> 00:38:40.329
By this you know the spirit of
God: every spirit that confesses

00:38:40.329 --> 00:38:44.250
that Jesus Christ has come in
the flesh is from God,

00:38:44.250 --> 00:38:48.018
and every spirit that does not
confess Jesus is not from God,

00:38:48.018 --> 00:38:51.130
and this is the spirit of the
antichrist.

00:38:51.130 --> 00:38:53.911
One of the things that's going
on here--look at also 5:8,

00:38:53.911 --> 00:38:55.650
just briefly,
and we'll move on:

00:39:01.139 --> 00:39:03.882
These are three that testified:
the spirit and the water and

00:39:03.882 --> 00:39:04.440
the blood.
 

00:39:04.440 --> 00:39:05.639
And these three agree.
 

00:39:05.639 --> 00:39:08.202
In other words,
this author is objecting to

00:39:08.202 --> 00:39:11.619
some people who don't admit the
Messiahship of Jesus,

00:39:11.619 --> 00:39:13.710
and that may have been
reflected also in the Gospel.

00:39:13.710 --> 00:39:15.635
Remember some of the
reasons--some of the people

00:39:15.635 --> 00:39:18.134
there's a division is because
the writer of the Gospel of John

00:39:18.134 --> 00:39:20.755
believes that some people aren't
willing to confess that Jesus is

00:39:20.755 --> 00:39:22.335
divine,
that Jesus is the Messiah,

00:39:22.335 --> 00:39:23.340
that he's the Son of God.
 

00:39:23.340 --> 00:39:25.150
Now we get to a different
situation,

00:39:25.150 --> 00:39:28.315
apparently there are other
people who have now come up in

00:39:28.315 --> 00:39:31.253
the community who may be
accepting that Jesus was the

00:39:31.253 --> 00:39:34.420
Christ but they're denying that
he was fully human,

00:39:34.420 --> 00:39:35.869
they're denying that he was
flesh and blood,

00:39:35.869 --> 00:39:38.538
and actually we do see
different beginnings of

00:39:38.538 --> 00:39:40.079
different Christologies.
 

00:39:40.079 --> 00:39:42.690
The people--we have a term for
this,

00:39:42.690 --> 00:39:47.260
these early Christians who
said--they said that Jesus--

00:39:47.260 --> 00:39:49.166
maybe there was a human Jesus
but that's not really the

00:39:49.166 --> 00:39:52.032
Christ,
the Christ was this spirit that

00:39:52.032 --> 00:39:56.101
maybe looked like he was human--
in fact some of them said,

00:39:56.101 --> 00:39:58.882
well if he walked along a wet
beach he wouldn't leave

00:39:58.882 --> 00:40:01.505
footprints because he didn't
have a physical body,

00:40:01.505 --> 00:40:02.789
he just was spirit.
 

00:40:02.789 --> 00:40:07.875
He just seemed to be a body,
he seemed to be flesh and blood

00:40:07.875 --> 00:40:09.971
and that--
the Greek word for

00:40:09.971 --> 00:40:12.268
"seem"
he just looked like,

00:40:12.268 --> 00:40:15.650
we get this term we call
Docetics.

00:40:21.230 --> 00:40:24.639
Dokeo is the Greek word
for "to seem"

00:40:24.639 --> 00:40:28.307
or "to look like,"
so other Christians used this

00:40:28.307 --> 00:40:31.590
term as a label for those
Christians who said,

00:40:31.590 --> 00:40:33.489
Jesus wasn't truly flesh and
blood,

00:40:33.489 --> 00:40:35.179
because how can a divine being
be flesh and blood?

00:40:35.179 --> 00:40:36.690
That's a contradiction in terms.
 

00:40:36.690 --> 00:40:39.722
You can't have a being that's
both God and flesh and blood

00:40:39.722 --> 00:40:42.650
because flesh and blood rots and
dies, and goes away.

00:40:42.650 --> 00:40:45.235
God is eternal,
so God by definition can't be

00:40:45.235 --> 00:40:47.175
flesh and blood,
and so they said,

00:40:47.175 --> 00:40:50.760
if Jesus is divine he must not
have been flesh and blood.

00:40:50.760 --> 00:40:53.340
He must have just seemed like
he was flesh and blood.

00:40:53.340 --> 00:40:57.402
Other Christians said,
that's wrong and they call

00:40:57.402 --> 00:41:00.619
these people the
"Seemsters,"

00:41:00.619 --> 00:41:01.719
Docetics.
 

00:41:01.719 --> 00:41:05.668
Docetism refers to a
Christology that says Jesus is

00:41:05.668 --> 00:41:07.672
spirit;
the Christ is spirit,

00:41:07.672 --> 00:41:10.010
but not really flesh and blood
human.

00:41:10.010 --> 00:41:13.606
Notice how this author is
arguing against different kinds

00:41:13.606 --> 00:41:17.590
of ideas and it shows a further
split in early Christianity.

00:41:17.590 --> 00:41:20.536
You have some people believing
that Jesus was human but not

00:41:20.536 --> 00:41:22.936
fully divine,
other people believing that he

00:41:22.936 --> 00:41:25.159
was so divine that he wasn't
even human,

00:41:25.159 --> 00:41:28.730
and this author is trying to
hold together these two things.

00:41:28.730 --> 00:41:31.489
Now how this happened--so
that's what's going on,

00:41:31.489 --> 00:41:34.974
the Gospel--the first letter of
John shows a community that's

00:41:34.974 --> 00:41:38.170
again divided but now it's
divided by some of the people

00:41:38.170 --> 00:41:41.250
within its midst going off
because they thought,

00:41:41.250 --> 00:41:43.530
you can't have a flesh and
blood God,

00:41:43.530 --> 00:41:45.494
and therefore,
if you're going to have Jesus

00:41:45.494 --> 00:41:47.230
as God he can't be flesh and
blood,

00:41:47.230 --> 00:41:50.500
so they've left the community.
 

00:41:50.500 --> 00:41:52.630
Let's look at 2 John,
this is a little--

00:41:52.630 --> 00:41:55.862
I'm going to read all the way
through this one because this is

00:41:55.862 --> 00:41:57.391
going--
we need to sort of figure out

00:41:57.391 --> 00:41:58.010
what's going on.
 

00:41:58.010 --> 00:41:59.030
It's a very short letter.
 

00:41:59.030 --> 00:42:02.172
"The elder,"
so he calls himself the elder,

00:42:02.172 --> 00:42:04.469
so he doesn't even give us his
name.

00:42:04.469 --> 00:42:06.480
The elder to the elect lady and
her children,

00:42:06.480 --> 00:42:09.528
whom I love in the truth,
and not only I but also all who

00:42:09.528 --> 00:42:11.976
know the truth,
because of the truth that

00:42:11.976 --> 00:42:14.619
abides in us and will be with us
forever ...

00:42:14.619 --> 00:42:17.300
I was overjoyed to find some of
your children walking in the

00:42:17.300 --> 00:42:19.710
truth just as we have been
commanded by the Father.

00:42:19.710 --> 00:42:21.726
He's talking to an elect lady
and her children,

00:42:21.726 --> 00:42:24.005
most of us think this is a
metaphor and he's actually

00:42:24.005 --> 00:42:25.409
addressing this to a church.
 

00:42:25.409 --> 00:42:27.831
The elect lady probably means
the church itself,

00:42:27.831 --> 00:42:30.715
not a particular human person,
but that's just a judgment

00:42:30.715 --> 00:42:31.179
call.
 

00:42:31.179 --> 00:42:34.068
But now, dear lady,
I ask you not as though I were

00:42:34.068 --> 00:42:37.309
writing to you a new commandment
but one we had from the

00:42:37.309 --> 00:42:39.610
beginning, let us love one
another.

00:42:39.610 --> 00:42:41.748
There's that love thing,
so we're know we're still in

00:42:41.748 --> 00:42:44.260
the same kind of Christianity
that we were with the others.

00:42:44.260 --> 00:42:46.757
This is love,
that we walk according to his

00:42:46.757 --> 00:42:48.731
commandments;
this is the commandment that

00:42:48.731 --> 00:42:50.199
you have heard from the
beginning ...

00:42:50.199 --> 00:42:52.780
Many deceivers have gone out
into the world,

00:42:52.780 --> 00:42:56.199
those who do not confess that
Jesus Christ has come in the

00:42:56.199 --> 00:42:56.800
flesh.
 

00:42:56.800 --> 00:43:00.190
[There are those people again.]
Any such person is the deceiver

00:43:00.190 --> 00:43:01.340
and the antichrist.
 

00:43:01.340 --> 00:43:04.389
Be on your guard so that you do
not lose what we have worked for

00:43:04.389 --> 00:43:05.940
but may receive a full reward.
 

00:43:05.940 --> 00:43:08.876
Everyone who does not abide in
the teaching of Christ but goes

00:43:08.876 --> 00:43:10.320
beyond it does not have God.
 

00:43:10.320 --> 00:43:13.280
Whoever abides in the teaching
has both the Father and the Son.

00:43:13.280 --> 00:43:16.878
Do not receive into the house
or welcome anyone who comes to

00:43:16.878 --> 00:43:19.320
you and does not bring this
teaching,

00:43:19.320 --> 00:43:22.094
for to welcome is to
participate in the evil deeds of

00:43:22.094 --> 00:43:22.949
such a person.
 

00:43:22.949 --> 00:43:26.489
The main purpose of this very
short letter is to say,

00:43:26.489 --> 00:43:29.235
to another church that's in the
same kind of community with this

00:43:29.235 --> 00:43:30.942
one,
there are people who have left

00:43:30.942 --> 00:43:33.701
our community and the reason is
they don't believe Jesus was

00:43:33.701 --> 00:43:34.869
fully flesh and blood.
 

00:43:34.869 --> 00:43:37.710
Don't even let them come to
visit you,

00:43:37.710 --> 00:43:39.639
these are traveling preachers,
and he says,

00:43:39.639 --> 00:43:41.280
don't receive them,
don't give them money,

00:43:41.280 --> 00:43:43.324
don't give them food,
don't put them up in your guest

00:43:43.324 --> 00:43:45.686
room,
just completely shun them,

00:43:45.686 --> 00:43:49.699
so he's writing to another
church because of this.

00:43:49.699 --> 00:43:52.445
Now look at 3 John:
"The elder to the beloved

00:43:52.445 --> 00:43:55.190
Gaius," now it's the same
person writing,

00:43:55.190 --> 00:43:57.090
he says, but now it's to a man
named Gaius,

00:43:57.090 --> 00:43:59.469
not to the elect lady.
 

00:43:59.469 --> 00:44:02.369
I pray that all may go with
you, in good health ...

00:44:02.369 --> 00:44:05.364
Beloved, you do faithfully
whatever you do for the friends,

00:44:05.364 --> 00:44:07.429
even though they are strangers
to you.

00:44:07.429 --> 00:44:09.010
They have testified to your
love before the church.

00:44:09.010 --> 00:44:12.610
You will do well to send them
on in a manner worthy of God,

00:44:12.610 --> 00:44:15.217
for they began their journey
for the sake of Christ accepting

00:44:15.217 --> 00:44:16.610
no support from non-believers.
 

00:44:16.610 --> 00:44:18.559
This is a letter that has been
sent around,

00:44:18.559 --> 00:44:21.159
probably with other traveling
preachers,

00:44:21.159 --> 00:44:24.668
but these traveling preachers
seem to be representatives of

00:44:24.668 --> 00:44:26.829
the elder himself,
the author.

00:44:26.829 --> 00:44:28.923
He's writing to a man named
Gaius and says,

00:44:28.923 --> 00:44:31.168
you're a good guy,
you receive our messengers,

00:44:31.168 --> 00:44:34.309
you receive the people that
we're sending around to preach.

00:44:34.309 --> 00:44:36.204
"I have written something
to the church"

00:44:36.204 --> 00:44:38.204
--
oh he did write a letter to the

00:44:38.204 --> 00:44:40.324
church,
so now you see he wrote another

00:44:40.324 --> 00:44:42.956
letter to the church,
he's writing this letter to an

00:44:42.956 --> 00:44:43.539
individual.
 

00:44:43.539 --> 00:44:47.396
"But Diotrephes,
who likes to put himself first,

00:44:47.396 --> 00:44:50.139
does not acknowledge our
authority.

00:44:50.139 --> 00:44:52.070
So if I come"--in other
words,

00:44:52.070 --> 00:44:56.152
Diotrephes seems to be the
leader of a church and has not

00:44:56.152 --> 00:45:00.090
allowed the elder to send his
letter to that church.

00:45:00.090 --> 00:45:03.579
He's intercepting letters and
not allowing these things to be

00:45:03.579 --> 00:45:05.150
read aloud in the church.
 

00:45:05.150 --> 00:45:07.239
All these letters were supposed
to be read aloud in churches.

00:45:07.239 --> 00:45:10.746
If I come I will call attention
to what he is doing in spreading

00:45:10.746 --> 00:45:12.250
false charges against us.
 

00:45:12.250 --> 00:45:14.867
And not content with these
charges, he refuses to welcome

00:45:14.867 --> 00:45:17.483
the friends and even prevents
those who want to do so and

00:45:17.483 --> 00:45:18.980
expels them from the church.
 

00:45:18.980 --> 00:45:24.262
Diotrephes is refusing to
welcome the messengers from the

00:45:24.262 --> 00:45:30.112
elder that the elder sent ahead
of himself with the letter that

00:45:30.112 --> 00:45:32.000
makes up 2 John.
 

00:45:32.000 --> 00:45:34.380
You see what's going on here?
 

00:45:34.380 --> 00:45:36.699
There's a leader of this
Johannine church,

00:45:36.699 --> 00:45:39.190
probably after the writing of
the Gospel,

00:45:39.190 --> 00:45:41.030
probably after the writing of 1
John,

00:45:41.030 --> 00:45:44.313
and he writes 2 John as a sort
of introductory letter to a

00:45:44.313 --> 00:45:45.672
church,
and he says,

00:45:45.672 --> 00:45:48.280
I'm sending you some of my
messengers,

00:45:48.280 --> 00:45:50.760
receive them,
listen to the letter,

00:45:50.760 --> 00:45:52.699
give them what they need,
help them out financially,

00:45:52.699 --> 00:45:55.646
put them up in your guest room,
and then send them on their way

00:45:55.646 --> 00:45:58.309
so they can travel around to
other Christian churches.

00:45:58.309 --> 00:46:01.989
Something's gone wrong though,
maybe this is a different--

00:46:01.989 --> 00:46:04.309
maybe 3 John--we don't know,
this is speculation,

00:46:04.309 --> 00:46:08.476
maybe 3 John is another letter
that he had to write to an

00:46:08.476 --> 00:46:12.420
individual in that town because
2 John didn't work.

00:46:12.420 --> 00:46:13.768
Why?
 

00:46:13.768 --> 00:46:16.123
It may be that those people
disagreed with him about his

00:46:16.123 --> 00:46:18.838
Christology also,
so they may have received the

00:46:18.838 --> 00:46:22.170
very people that he thought they
shouldn't receive.

00:46:22.170 --> 00:46:26.329
And so he writes 3 John to an
individual saying,

00:46:26.329 --> 00:46:29.563
Diotrephes is causing a bunch
of problems not receiving my

00:46:29.563 --> 00:46:33.079
messengers and not allowing my
letters to be read in church.

00:46:33.079 --> 00:46:36.679
You see how this
represents--this is all guess

00:46:36.679 --> 00:46:37.239
work.
 

00:46:37.239 --> 00:46:40.806
We don't know what's going on
but we see several things about

00:46:40.806 --> 00:46:41.579
the letter.
 

00:46:41.579 --> 00:46:43.929
There's a greeting,
there are well wishes,

00:46:43.929 --> 00:46:46.503
there's praise of the
reputation and behavior of the

00:46:46.503 --> 00:46:49.092
recipients,
he attempts to establish a

00:46:49.092 --> 00:46:51.717
relationship,
he talks to this person--he's

00:46:51.717 --> 00:46:54.847
the father's son or a patron
client relationship and there's

00:46:54.847 --> 00:46:56.440
a letter of recommendation.
 

00:46:56.440 --> 00:46:58.021
Send them on,
this is what you do in the

00:46:58.021 --> 00:46:59.764
ancient world,
you give a messenger--there's

00:46:59.764 --> 00:47:00.900
no post office you know.
 

00:47:00.900 --> 00:47:04.208
You give a letter to someone
who's traveling and that person

00:47:04.208 --> 00:47:06.789
gets to a friend of yours to
where it says,

00:47:06.789 --> 00:47:09.150
and they show the letter,
that letter is read outside--

00:47:09.150 --> 00:47:12.492
read aloud to the group,
and then you put that person up

00:47:12.492 --> 00:47:15.244
or those people up,
you host them for a while,

00:47:15.244 --> 00:47:17.420
they talk and you share your
messages,

00:47:17.420 --> 00:47:19.360
and then you send them on--you
give them a little bit of

00:47:19.360 --> 00:47:21.510
financial support to send them
on their way to the rest of the

00:47:21.510 --> 00:47:21.900
travel.
 

00:47:21.900 --> 00:47:25.036
That's clearly what is going on
and both of these letters are

00:47:25.036 --> 00:47:27.335
letters of recommendation,
typical letters of

00:47:27.335 --> 00:47:28.329
recommendation.
 

00:47:28.329 --> 00:47:33.994
What makes it interesting is
that 2 John seems to have been a

00:47:33.994 --> 00:47:38.809
letter of recommendation that
didn't work, maybe.

00:47:38.809 --> 00:47:42.666
And then 3 John had to be
written to an individual because

00:47:42.666 --> 00:47:46.320
his letter couldn't get through
to the whole church.

00:47:46.320 --> 00:47:50.050
What's the cause of this
division?

00:47:50.050 --> 00:47:53.722
Clearly the cause of division
in the Gospel of John is that

00:47:53.722 --> 00:47:57.460
some people are not accepting a
high enough Christology,

00:47:57.460 --> 00:47:59.809
they're not accepting that
Jesus is truly divine.

00:47:59.809 --> 00:48:02.958
They might be accepting that
Jesus is human but not that he

00:48:02.958 --> 00:48:03.610
is divine.
 

00:48:03.610 --> 00:48:07.530
The situation has shifted
slightly by the time we get to

00:48:07.530 --> 00:48:09.902
the 1 John,
the letter, because there it

00:48:09.902 --> 00:48:12.744
seems like yes he's talked about
some people are antichrist

00:48:12.744 --> 00:48:15.539
because they've denied that
Jesus is the Messiah but other

00:48:15.539 --> 00:48:18.331
people are antichrist because
they've denied that Jesus is

00:48:18.331 --> 00:48:18.969
flesh.
 

00:48:18.969 --> 00:48:22.139
He says they have gone out from
among us,

00:48:22.139 --> 00:48:25.521
so the church has been split
again on the issue of

00:48:25.521 --> 00:48:29.318
Christology but now the
Christology is do you accept the

00:48:29.318 --> 00:48:33.025
full fleshness of Jesus,
but then when you get to 2 John

00:48:33.025 --> 00:48:36.710
and 3 John,
the split--is the split now

00:48:36.710 --> 00:48:37.920
doctrinal?
 

00:48:37.920 --> 00:48:39.670
Is it Christological?
 

00:48:39.670 --> 00:48:42.920
Or is this just a split over
who gets to be the leader?

00:48:42.920 --> 00:48:46.039
Who gets to be the recognized
leader of these churches?

00:48:46.039 --> 00:48:48.018
Is it the elder?
 

00:48:48.018 --> 00:48:51.630
Do his letters have to be
accepted and his emissaries get

00:48:51.630 --> 00:48:53.760
accepted in different churches?
 

00:48:53.760 --> 00:48:55.730
Or is it this guy Diotrephes?
 

00:48:55.730 --> 00:48:58.530
Is he sort of trying to buck
the elder for the leadership?

00:48:58.530 --> 00:49:01.690
Is there a dispute over
Christology?

00:49:01.690 --> 00:49:04.686
Do they disagree about
Christology or is it now a

00:49:04.686 --> 00:49:07.059
purely a personnel leadership
issue?

00:49:07.059 --> 00:49:11.641
It's very difficult to see but
you can very quickly see by

00:49:11.641 --> 00:49:15.260
looking at these four different
documents,

00:49:15.260 --> 00:49:18.619
the Gospel of John,
1 John, 2 John,

00:49:18.619 --> 00:49:21.878
3 John, four different
documents which may have been

00:49:21.878 --> 00:49:23.867
written in the--
not by the same person,

00:49:23.867 --> 00:49:25.909
we don't think they're all
written by the same person,

00:49:25.909 --> 00:49:28.108
but they're clearly written by
the same school of early

00:49:28.108 --> 00:49:28.719
Christianity.
 

00:49:28.719 --> 00:49:30.949
They share enough the
vocabulary and enough theology.

00:49:30.949 --> 00:49:34.358
You can almost see four
different stages of development

00:49:34.358 --> 00:49:36.570
and you see what we might
expect.

00:49:36.570 --> 00:49:38.974
Remember I said that in growing
up in Texas we always said

00:49:38.974 --> 00:49:41.380
"let's make like a Baptist
church and split."

00:49:41.380 --> 00:49:46.402
Early churches also seem to
split a lot, is that what we see

00:49:46.402 --> 00:49:47.000
here?
 

00:49:47.000 --> 00:49:50.021
Four different stages of a
church with different kinds of

00:49:50.021 --> 00:49:52.503
divisions happening and,
therefore different,

00:49:52.503 --> 00:49:54.753
kinds of Christianity
developing due to these

00:49:54.753 --> 00:49:57.070
divisions;
very possible.

00:49:57.070 --> 00:49:59.360
Any questions about that?
 

00:49:59.360 --> 00:50:01.250
Questions, comments, outbursts?
 

00:50:01.250 --> 00:50:06.103
Now what I've just given you is
one reading of these texts,

00:50:06.103 --> 00:50:09.199
and I've done a lot of
speculating.

00:50:09.199 --> 00:50:10.492
For example,
you could just say,

00:50:10.492 --> 00:50:12.869
well 2 John may have been
written to one church and 3 John

00:50:12.869 --> 00:50:15.329
is written to a totally
different geographical region,

00:50:15.329 --> 00:50:16.518
that's entirely possible.
 

00:50:16.518 --> 00:50:19.561
I think it's interesting to put
them in this way and read them

00:50:19.561 --> 00:50:21.501
this way,
but that's just one historical

00:50:21.501 --> 00:50:24.409
reconstruction because a lot of
what I'm teaching you is let's--

00:50:24.409 --> 00:50:27.280
how do you imagine history
developing if all you have are

00:50:27.280 --> 00:50:29.947
these texts by which you
construct the history of the

00:50:29.947 --> 00:50:30.820
early church?
 

00:50:30.820 --> 00:50:34.067
Next time we're going to shift
gears dramatically because now

00:50:34.067 --> 00:50:37.260
we're not going to be talking
about the historical situation

00:50:37.260 --> 00:50:39.914
of the text,
we're going to be talking about

00:50:39.914 --> 00:50:43.382
how do you get through all these
texts to try to figure out the

00:50:43.382 --> 00:50:44.949
historical Jesus himself?
 

00:50:44.949 --> 00:50:47.699
Did Jesus of Nazareth really
exist?

00:50:47.699 --> 00:50:49.820
What did he do?
 

00:50:49.820 --> 00:50:50.849
What did he say?
 

00:50:50.849 --> 00:50:52.849
What did he think of himself?
 

00:50:52.849 --> 00:50:55.150
That's what we'll talk about
